Guard libiberty/pex-unix.c spawn block with defined(_P_NOWAITO).
On macOS, configure detects spawnve and spawnvpe but _P_NOWAITO is
only available on Windows/Cygwin via <process.h>.  Without the guard,
the spawn implementation block is compiled on macOS but fails because
_P_NOWAITO is undeclared.  Adding defined(_P_NOWAITO) to the #if
condition causes macOS builds to skip the Cygwin-only spawn path and
fall through to the standard vfork/fork implementation instead.
--- a/libiberty/pex-unix.c
+++ b/libiberty/pex-unix.c
@@ -366,7 +366,7 @@ pex_unix_close (struct pex_obj *obj ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED, int fd)
 
 /* Execute a child.  */
 
-#if defined(HAVE_SPAWNVE) && defined(HAVE_SPAWNVPE)
+#if defined(HAVE_SPAWNVE) && defined(HAVE_SPAWNVPE) && defined(_P_NOWAITO)
 /* Implementation of pex->exec_child using the Cygwin spawn operation.  */
 
 /* Subroutine of pex_unix_exec_child.  Move OLD_FD to a new file descriptor
